Class AdobeAssetFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.storage.asset.AdobeAssetInternal
      • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobeAsset
        • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobeAssetFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.storage.AdobeAssetFileInternal

    public class AdobeAssetFile
extends AdobeAsset
implements java.io.Externalizable
    AdobeAssetFile represents the file handler of a file in Creative Cloud which can be used to get thumbnail rendition of the file. It allows creating files in the Creative Cloud and also to read their details (type, size, etc) .

      • create

        public static AdobeAssetFile create(java.lang.String name,
                                    AdobeAssetFolder parentFolder,
                                    java.net.URL localFileURL,
                                    java.lang.String type,
                                    IAdobeGenericRequestCallback<AdobeAssetFile,com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.utils.AdobeCSDKException> createDelegate,
                                    android.os.Handler callBackRequiredForHandler)
        Creates and uploads a file into the Adobe Creative Cloud asynchronously.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the file.
        parentFolder - the enclosing folder of the file.
        localFileURL - the local URL that stores the data for the file.
        type - the content-type of the file.The content type for all types of files are listed at http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml.
        createDelegate - IAdobeGenericRequestCallback<AdobeAssetFile,AdobeAssetException> handler to handle completion, error , cancellation and tracking progress.
        callBackRequiredForHandler - optional parameter. If not null the callback gets posted on the handler event queue.
        Returns:
        a placeholder pointer to the AdobeAssetFile.
